{"media":{"disableImageZooming":false},"solution":{"sample":"<div>A translation memory can be seen as a collection of source texts aligned with their target texts at segment level, and stored in a way that makes it easy to retrieve an existing translation for a given source segment, if that source segment happens to come up again in a translation job. &nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>A translation memory is thus a collection of translation <strong>data <\/strong>that are stored in a way that makes reuse of translated segments easy. Translation memories are commonly stored using tmx format.<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>A translation memory <strong>tool <\/strong>is a software application that is used to create, update and manage translation memories.&nbsp;Translation memory tools may be offered as part of a more complex \"translation environment\" or \"translation management system\", in which other tools are also made available to the translator.<\/div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div>Well-known translation memory tools include those that come with Trados Studio, Memsource and MemoQ, to name just three.<\/div>\n","introduction":""},"keywords":[{"options":{"points":1,"occurrences":1,"caseSensitive":false,"forgiveMistakes":false,"feedbackIncludedWord":"keyword","feedbackMissedWord":"none"},"keyword":"segment","alternatives":["segments"]},{"options":{"points":1,"occurrences":1,"caseSensitive":true,"forgiveMistakes":false,"feedbackIncludedWord":"keyword","feedbackMissedWord":"none"},"keyword":"translation unit","alternatives":["translation units","TU"]},{"options":{"points":1,"occurrences":1,"caseSensitive":true,"forgiveMistakes":false,"feedbackIncludedWord":"keyword","feedbackMissedWord":"none"},"keyword":"data"},{"options":{"points":1,"occurrences":1,"caseSensitive":true,"forgiveMistakes":false,"feedbackIncludedWord":"keyword","feedbackMissedWord":"none"},"keyword":"software"},{"options":{"points":1,"occurrences":1,"caseSensitive":true,"forgiveMistake